OL,3,CCumberland adult social care 'requires
OL,4,Cimprovement'
OL,6,FChris Badger, CQC chief inspector of
OL,7,Fadult social care and integrated care,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Cumberland Council needed to
OL,9,Fmake improvements in how it's
OL,10,Fproviding adult social care to people
OL,11,Fliving in the area.
OL,13,F"While we saw strong partnership
OL,14,Fworking and genuine commitment to
OL,15,Fperson-centred care, the local
OL,16,Fauthority does have further work to do
OL,17,Fto ensure people are consistently
OL,18,Freceiving the support they need.
